Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise's heart was blooming more with each day \Nfrom having her loving mother always by her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As for Lotte, she started \Ntaking piano lessons from her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.21,0:01:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The two that switched places had finally \Ncome to realise the bright sides of their new lives. {lit: their daily life changed to great}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.03,0:01:59.03,Sign,,0,0,125,,{\c&HE8FEFB&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 11 \N {\fs35} Little Detective Agency {小さな探偵団} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.21,0:02:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Sunday morning, \Nso dad is probably still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.92,0:02:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try not to wake him while we clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.69,0:02:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! A complete disarray!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, in moderato!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.82,0:02:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"Luise, I know you'll be here in the morning again. {lit: good job as always - I hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.26,0:03:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working this whole night, and the only reason \NI went to sleep was because I passed out. {lit: I intend to sleep until I faint/pass out - I hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.80,0:03:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I intend to get my sleep now, so until I'm a hundred years old, \Nplease don't wake me up."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.67,0:03:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundred years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Also, a letter for you, \Nsupposed to be delivered on Rotenturmstraße,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently got mixed with correspondence \Nbound for this address." {to disappear into; to slip into; to be lost in; to be mixed up with}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Lotte! I'm going to the office now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck! \NWhen will you be home?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.46,0:03:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. I don't think we'll have \Nthe work up to our eyeballs today,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so I should be home by noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right, right. \NA letter had arrived for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.71,0:03:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.76,0:03:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom might it be from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's letters are supposed to be in General Delivery. {/stay in the post office}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my dad and mom breaking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, dad fell in love with another woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she's not taking it too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Lotte, are you doing fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.79,0:04:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm writing to say my dad and mom \Nmanaged to reconcile."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? They reconciled?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.59,0:04:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom had noticed, that dad \Nsneaks out of the house every night,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so she was steadfastly convinced \Nhe is visiting his paramour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.53,0:04:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality, dad was just looking for a way to lose weight, \Nso he picked up karate classes again. {narai is as is habit; the way life normally is so I'm not entirely sure what it's here}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And he didn't tell to a single soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.63,0:04:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, dad never managed \Nto lose even an ounce of weight through karate,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.93,0:04:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but during his row with mom, \Nhe actually lost some due to uneasiness. {/thanks to quarreling with mom}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But as soon as they reconciled, \Nhe started eating plentifully, just like before! {(eating) heartily}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.08,0:05:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, I guess losing some weight \Nwill forever remain a pipe dream," he said! {/never again I will think of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy for you, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.81,0:05:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, already done cleaning up in the atelier?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was about to do groceries, \N so would look after the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.29,0:05:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Palfy is listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.73,0:05:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, I'm looking for my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.13,0:05:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anyone named Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.54,0:05:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Luise here. It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Nobody else is home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.31,0:05:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're calling like that... \NSomething happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.64,0:06:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all! \NI got a letter from Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so surprised! I bet, this very minute \Nall her friends from the summer camp feel the same! {to be amazed; to be shocked; to be astonished; to be astounded; to be disgusted; to be exasperated; to be fed up} {not really sure what to make of kono bun ja} {actually just "all the kids from the summer camp" but that would be overkill}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.61,0:06:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie's lucky, don't you think? {/it's good for ... isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.85,0:06:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.95,0:06:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If only our dad and mom \Nwould also reconcile, one way or another...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.30,0:06:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you curious about why did our dad and mom \Nbreak up in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.73,0:06:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking, it could be because of a misunderstanding, \Njust like in Stephie's case!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are constantly in a hurry, \Nthey always jump to the wrong conclusions! {choko is quickly and easily​so I think she might mean "always on the run/in motion" but might also be "impertinent; impudent; saucy; cheeky"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.48,0:06:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you... Do you suppose, \Nif it was really due to misunderstanding...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.84,0:06:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.64,0:06:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think they can reconcile, too?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.90,0:06:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! They should be able to reconcile!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.13,0:06:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, how about we try to investigate \Nthe cause of dad and mom's break-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to their own explanations! {/ask directly}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.20,0:06:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as it would help to reconcile them, \NI won't stop at anything! {/I can ask anything - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... So do I!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.57,0:06:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask him! The reason for break-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.63,0:07:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Mozart is amazing, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he manage to give birth to a tune that enthralling \Ninto a world that mundane?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to ask him now. \NWhy did he break up with mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.39,0:07:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your morning clean-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.67,0:07:55.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,Dad, I need to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:07:57.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.86,0:08:01.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,Don't try to evade the question. \NPut it frankly! {to dodge (e.g. a question); to evade; to sidestep}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.10,0:08:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, oh my, how intimidating. \NWould you look at that. {no clue what he means by ittegoran}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's no use. I can't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to muster some courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.21,0:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.54,0:08:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... That is... If you don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did Mozart only give birth to enthralling tunes \Ninto this mundane world?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.60,0:08:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what concerns you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.97,0:08:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... no. Actually, not! What I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.01,0:08:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, got it. Will be there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I have to go now \Nto conduct a final general rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, I want you to show up as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal? Make sure to free up some time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.13,0:09:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Dad, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.01,0:09:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I forget! The reason Mozart \Ngave birth to such enthralling tunes -
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's rather simple, \Nhe was a genius of about the same magnitude as your dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Will this suffice for an answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.17,0:09:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just impossible. For me at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.70,0:09:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could she be the reason behind dad and mom's parting?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.31,0:09:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. So you've been fond \Nof that Palfy gent for some time? {no clue what this whole convo is, lit is "you liked mr. palfy/palfy's family"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:10:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me correct you there, father. {/it's a bit different}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.29,0:10:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mere "fondness" doesn't do it justice. {just liking is not enough - wtf???}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My fixation on him is out of this world. {like, like it's unbearable/cannot help (doing); cannot but do; anxious to do; cannot get enough of - wtaff?!?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.18,0:10:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, Frau Gerlach...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what was Palfy's reaction to that? {hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.56,0:10:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, for the last ten years, he only had one woman in mind \Nwhile giving birth to his music. {lit: about that, in those 10 years he was giving birth to music for the sake of one woman - still fucking clueless}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one woman? \NThat must have been you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, it's been only half a year \Nsince we got to know each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.90,0:10:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? \NWho, then, might that woman be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.10,0:10:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you up to, in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.41,0:10:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.87,0:10:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking to the boy serving tea. {lit: I'm drinking tea - no FUCKING clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What a weird kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me tell you, this is highly ignoble of Palfy. {outrageous; scandalous; inexcusable; disgraceful; shameful; rude; unreasonable​}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Being infatuated with another woman, \Nwhile having you around. {to leave as is; to let alone; to disregard you, being absorbed in; immersed in; crazy about; obsessed with; devoted to another woman}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, most certainly, \Nseveral orders younger and prettier than her!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.28,0:10:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is as clear as a day, Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, his ex-wife might also have a clue \Nof who this woman is. {/it seems, his ... also knows this woman - unsure if it's a question or a statement}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:11:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you also suppose that woman \Nmight have been what precipitated Palfy's divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.19,0:11:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I had any idea, \NI would have given her a mouthful long ago! {lit: if I understood, I'd bully her especially}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.76,0:11:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigating the reason \Nbehind your dad and mom's divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, it's like Luise \Nhad opened her little detective agency, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.47,0:11:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Little detective agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.51,0:11:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm nowhere near that talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that woman Frau Gerlach mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.94,0:11:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I even start looking into it - \NI don't have a single clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then we'll run this little detective agency together, \Nwith joint efforts! {/we'll be two little detectives}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Hans?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.20,0:12:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on now, Resi! \NEavesdropping, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.43,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know exactly who that woman is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, when cleaning up in Master's atelier, \NI noticed a diary in a brown binding. {no clue whats kawa in "chairo kawa ni"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.41,0:12:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You peeked into dad's diary, didn't you? {/without permission}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in my life! I just glanced over it \Nand spotted some scribblings, accidentally. {scribbling; scrawl; hasty writing}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It said "Pamina."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Pamina?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.85,0:12:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I closed it immediately after, \Nso that's really all I've seen. I swear, it's the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it? {/truth, is it} \NMaybe you glanced over anything else? {/looked a bit more didn't you}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.39,0:12:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if only a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, my passion springs eternal, Pamina. \NIn all my life, I only loved you."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.10,0:12:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a photo included, too! \NBut when I tried to look at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a bolt from the blue, \NMaster returned at that exact moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like a pretty scrupulous "quick glance." {/you inspected it thoroughly didn't you}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlikely! {guess, maybe "unintentionally; subconsciously; by mistake; against one's better judgement (judgment)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Ah... Wait, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.31,0:12:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.96,0:13:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait, Hans!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.48,0:13:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go there and look for the diary ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.32,0:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't do that kind of thing! \NThe contents of dad's diary are private... {/dad wrote ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll just look at her photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.65,0:13:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Hans!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.68,0:13:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to find out, or not, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason behind your dad and mom's parting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not ready to go as far \Nas peeking into his diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.75,0:13:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's strike a deal. \NWe'll only search three places for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.78,0:13:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't find it still, \Nthen have it your way. {/we give up}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.61,0:13:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Even if I myself would have liked \Nto know Herr Palfy better out of my huge respect, {have a huge respect/esteem for ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.98,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if the price for it is Luise's disappointment, I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.96,0:13:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I just realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:13:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.72,0:14:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want it, we don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.76,0:14:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to gloom over that. {to be discouraged; to be disheartened}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.89,0:14:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If we search in only one place...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.78,0:14:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Might be over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.85,0:14:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was up to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.43,0:14:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.60,0:14:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And where's the lock?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.70,0:14:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That might be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This casket, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.84,0:14:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our one place! \NLet's {open it and }look inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.04,0:14:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But promise me that we'll back off after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure it'll fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.98,0:15:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It it doesn't, so much for an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.15,0:15:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm opening it, ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.07,0:15:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.16,0:15:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I changed my mind! {we shouldn'tafter all}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.69,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, dad is such a prankster! \NIt's like he always knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.40,0:15:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your investigation concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.07,0:16:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so it finally went off? {/you opened it}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I spent a good hour \Nchoosing the most conspicuous spot for the scare box,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.91,0:16:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but Luise kept avoiding it, \Nas though on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.36,0:16:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought I'd need to choose a new spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But dad, why did you return so soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.43,0:16:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? It's for this. Forgot the main score \Nfor tonight's big concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! And that must be \NHans of the Winds, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise had told me some about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.86,0:16:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Honored to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.20,0:16:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, speaking of which,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.69,0:16:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you're coming to listen to tonight's big concert \Nalongside Luise, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless... You've planned a date just for two?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.91,0:16:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.18,0:16:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one fantastic dad you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.15,0:17:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere in this opera hall, \NFrau Pamina is listening, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This concert, too... \NAre you conducting it for Frau Pamina{, too}, dad? {/music, are you plaing ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.14,0:17:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, I should take a quick look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll return it tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.45,0:17:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, are you still awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.21,0:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you seemed gloomier than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.33,0:18:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.14,0:18:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can't help worrying, if I was the one \Nwho upset my Luise somehow, even without realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.82,0:18:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you shouldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight's concert was excellent. \NI couldn't help getting deeply moved by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.51,0:18:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a honey to my ears!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.36,0:18:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Only when a profound affection for someone \Nis overflowing me, the greatest music is born.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only thanks to that emotion \Nthat I've been able to keep making music for ten years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.71,0:18:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. But I'm not feeling left out because of that. {hope its what she means by "I'm not lonely"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if all the space in dad's heart \Nis currently occupied by Frau Pamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.18,0:18:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Pamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Frau Pamina a good person?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what this all about, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be mistaken to think that Pamina was the one \NI cherished for those ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it would also be wrong to say \NI'm not one bit concerned about Pamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, it's nothing new, \Nas music fans are in love with her all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.65,0:19:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Pamina would remain a celebrity for all times. {/eternal masterpiece}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.03,0:19:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she's from Mozart's opera,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the heroine of The Magic Flute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But... Then... \NWho is the one that you cherish? {/loves}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She has loose curly hair, \Nand bright eyes, like two blue jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.35,0:19:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem is that lately, \Nvarious trifles often mislead her into feeling lonely. {lonely person; someone who easily succumbs to loneliness​}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.86,0:19:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you'll always be the prime source of my music.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.63,0:19:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight's concert was also my present of gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.93,0:19:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still uneasy? {to be troubled (by); to be bothered (by); to be inconvenienced (by)}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.99,0:19:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fantastic, dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:31.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eventually, just for a second, \NI couldn't help glancing into the brown diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.30,0:20:34.31,Sign,,0,0,0,,Turns out, it was not a diary at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.31,0:20:38.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,But instead, a complete libretto \Nof Mozart's Magic Flute opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.51,0:20:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, my love, Pamina..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But also... Also one another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.65,0:20:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I took the liberty to look at this precious photo, \Nsqueezed between last pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.54,0:20:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I never managed \Nto get to the bottom of dad and mom's parting. {/understand the reason}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.16,0:21:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's at least one thing I now know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.67,0:21:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad still remembers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.44,0:21:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,both of us. {/didn't forget about us two}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.37,0:21:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A report like this was something \NLotte would be willing to write daily, till the end of times, {absolutely no clue, lit: this manner/world/night, lotte continued to write reports forever}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.37,0:21:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling fully surrounded by the love of her amazing father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:21.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.41,0:23:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.78,0:23:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'm begging you! \NTry to dig out the truth behind dad and mom's parting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry, \NI'll definitely make mom answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.22,0:23:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that Frau Luise here \Ndoesn't tolerate those evading the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.72,0:23:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit, Luise! {force; vigor; vigour; energy; spirit; life}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.13,0:23:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit plays the decisive role in such matters. \NAlright, root for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't give up, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.63,0:23:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.07,0:23:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:\N The Secret Brought to Light. {to determine (esp. a culprit or underlying cause); to pin down; to ascertain; to locate; to identify}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.47,0:23:50.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 12 \N The Secret Brought to Light {to determine (esp. a culprit or underlying cause); to pin down; to ascertain; to locate; to identify} {秘密をつきとめた}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.47,0:23:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
